inn1.comm: oopsy! Tuffey loses his radar and the bowls wide outside leg stump, McCullum flings himself to his right and the ball goes towards fine leg
good length on middle and leg, pushed towards midwicket
wide down leg again
fuller on middle and leg and Hayden turns his wrists, midwicket does the fielding
Tuffey struggling here. this one is sprayed wide of off stump towards the direction of slip
good length on off stump, Hayden pushes forward and drives to mid-off
full on leg, Hayden gets forward just a touch and flicks it wide of midwicket a little uppishly
length ball on off stump, Hayden pushes it towards cover
straighter line and length, Hayden gets caught o the pads and a half herated appeal follows
Bond brings this shorter and Jaques defends off the backfoot
short of a length and Jaques lets that go
pitched up and swinging away, Jaques gets his bat forward, tries to drive without moving his feet, lucky not to get an edge
slightly short of a length, left alone
yorker length, ball is speared in full speed outside off and Jaques just gets some bat on it
Hayden steps down and lofts over mid-on and the fielder gets his hands up but the ball sails over him
Hayden goes over mid-off this time! gives the walk to the bowler and the elevation is even higher
Tuffey drops the length back, hayden swings across the line but the ball thuds onto his body
fuller and pushed in full force back to Tuffey who shows his agression by flinging the ball back to the batsman
swish and a miss! Hayden tries to flick it over midwicket, doesnt watch the ball, nearly misses the stumps
good length on off stump, Hayden curbs his agression and defends it towards covers
short of a length thudded on leg stump, comes in after pitching, Hayden gets back and across and defends back to Bond
good length on off stump, Hayden gets forward and pushes to cover, Bond varying his length here
good length on off, shapes away from  Hayden, a bit wide but Hayden lets it go
shapes away from Hayden again but Bond pitches this on middle and the ball doesnt deviate as much
similar delivery, pitching on middle, left alone
attempted yorker on middle and leg, Hayden gets in position to flick it on the on side but ends up placing it staright to square leg
good length outside off stump, left alone, not much seam movement
slightly fuller on middle and leg, Hayden gets forward and turns it wide of midwicket
left alone to Mccullum
good length on off stump, Hayden tries to flick across the line and the ball gets the inside edge and goes towards fine leg
width offered outside off, hayden pushes it wide of cover, Taylor chases hard and just fails to pull it back, does a tumble at the boundary
pitched closer to the batsman, defended off the backfoot
Bond errs in line for the first time, bowls just wide of off stump
better line, closer to off stump, shaping away a little, left alone
just short of a full length, Jaques watchfully lets it go to McCullum

that was inevitable! Bond bangs it in short of a length on middle, the bqll shapes away, Jaques doesnt move his feet towards the line of the ball, plays away from the body and the edge flies to Fleming at second slip who takes it at waist height
and nearly another! overpitchesd on off stump and swinging away, Haddin stretches out and ghets a low edge which misses the slips, the ball carried but a difficult chance
defended back to the bowler
short of length on off stump, defended on the backfoot
pitched on a good length outside off stump, left alone
Tuffey's line goes awry, wide outside off stump and left alone
another poor delivery, Tuffey bowls it wide outside off again and worse, this was shorter
better, no swing, ball starightens after pitching outside off, Haddin defends comfortably on the backfoot
bowls this one a little fuller, draws Haddin on th e fronmt foot, pushed to the left of mid-off for a quick single
quick single taken towards mid-off, fielder has a shy at the stumps, hits but Hayden is home
stump to stump line from Bond, short of a length, defended back
fuller on leg, late swing, Hayden plays off his pads and the ball rolls towards fine leg
Bond holds the length back, thuds it outside off stump, Haddin lets it go
dug in short, the ball darts in after pitching, Haddin gets hit over thigh pads
pushed in faster, Haddin was beaten for pace
good length on off stump and Haddin this time gets some bat on it
strange sight, Gillespie pitches it on a good length on middle and leg, Hayden walks across, tries to flick but gets hit on the pads, appeal turned down
straighter and defended back to the bowler
pushed towards mid-off
aggression but with a price! Hayden plays it staright back to Gillespie who collects the ball, flings it back to the stumps, the bal rebounds and the batsmen steal a single courtesy the overthrow
fuller, swinging in, Haddin defends back to Gillespie
confidence! full, outside off and swingig away, Haddin steps forward and lofts over cover
short of a length outside off, angling across Hayden, left alone
that late away swing again, Bond pushes this a little fuller, hayden shoulders arms
good length on middle and leg, Hayden gets his bat down and defends
attempted yorker gone wrong, Hayden helps himself to a juicy full toss on the pads and turns it away past square leg, rare bad delivery
pushed wide of mid-on for a easy single
short of a length and defended back to the bowler
short and hayden pulls it straight to deep midwicket, extra protection at the boundary
back of a length putside off, pushed towards covers
back of a length again and Haddin picks the length early and swings with his bottom hand, the ball sails over midwicket
the off side this time! overpitched on off stump and Haddin pierces the packed off side field
quick single taken towards mid-off, ball hits the stumps, Haddin dives but the third umpire rukes in the batsman's favour
pitched on the channel outside off, swinging away, left alone
slightly wider outside off stump, left alone to McCullum watchfully
dug in short of a length closer to off stump, left alone
Bond drops this one fuller, Haddin gets on the backfoot and defends
attempted inswinging yorker, Haddin digs it out and the ball hads towards point
pitched on a length outside off, not much movement after pitching. left alone

Gillespie has the last laugh! pitched up on off stump, Hayden steps down, gives himself some room to swish it over the off side, fails to get the desired elevation and hits it to Vettori at mid-off who takes it low
Hussey is greeted first up with a short of length delivery on off stump, left alone
defended back to the bowler
short of a length on middle, Hussey turns his wrists and turns it towards square leg
Hussey places it on the off side and cuts it to point
good work by Vincent at point, Haddin gets forwrd to a short of a length ball, CVincent flings himself to his right, aims at the non strikers end but the throw was too high
watchfully left alone
misfield at point, Gillepie at the deep throws it to the non strikers end and the ball strikes Hussey while he makes his ground
drive through covers, good timing by Hussey
better line by Hussey, pitches it closer to the batsman, Haddin gets back and defends on the off side
short, Gillespie hulrs it in with good pace, Hussey defends on the backfoot
slightly fuller, shaping across the left hander, Hussey pushes it towards point
good length on middle and off stump, defended back to the bowler
holds the length back a little, Hussey gets forward and triesd to work it past the off side, pushes it towwards point again
similar length, Hussey doesnt get enough room to steer it past the off side, defends to point again
fuller and Hussey tries to drive it straight, mistimes it as the ball gets the inner half the bat and rolls back to the bowler
loosener, pitches outside off, Haddin defends towards point
lapse in co0ncentration! Tuffey digs it in short as Haddin advances, misses it completely
fuller and turned towards midwicket
pitched closer to the batsman at a good length, Hussey gets forward and defends
fuller and just a touch slower, Hussey gets forward and ends up pushing it back to Tuffey
full on middle and off stump, Tuffey leans forward to drive but doesn't time it well enough, mid-off picks it up
well fielded at the deep backward point, Haddin backs away and slices a fullish delivery outside off, third man runs across to deep backward point and pulls it back
digs it in a little short and Haddin swings and.....misses
thundered past the bowler! full on off stump, Haddin hits it hard past the left of Gillespie who gets his hands towards the ball but it screams past him
outside off stump, staright to Styris at extra cover
swing and a miss, Haddin lucky not to get an edge
pulled away in style! Hussey picks the length so early, uses his bottom hand and whips it over square leg
pushed towards the off side
Tuffey aims at the blockhole on off stump, Haddin digs it out towards mid-on
slower ball, drifting on the pads, ball rolls towards fine leg
another cracker! Haddin charges a short of a length delivery, beats the off side field, the ball steams past cover
tries to do it again, the short ball catches Haddin on the hop, Haddin fortunately keeps it down, the ball rolls towards point
pushed towards the on side
Haddin charges down again, misses, was a little too short to play any strokes on the front foot
short and pulled towards fine leg
good length on middle and off, pushed towards cover
Hussey advances and goes over the top! the ball sails over mid off and cover
good length on middle stump, Hussey stays rooted to the crease this time and cuts to point
played towards poiht, Haddin takes off for a quick single, Vincent hits the stumps at the non strikers end
slower and fuller, Hussey drives back to Tuffey who gets a hand to it, good stop
what a shot! Hussey advances and lofts elegantly straight over the bowlers head
drifting on the pads and Hussey turns it away towards square leg
Haddin steps down again but doesnt get the desired timing, ball hits the inner edge and rolls to mid-on
drifting on the pads, ball clips the pad and rolls towards the on side
Vincent at point again! Hussey gives himself room  frees his arms but fails to pierce the off side field
short of a length outside off, Hussey finds the gap past point this time
Haddin hits it back to the bowler, cries of 'catch it'  but it was a bump ball
steps down and swings across the line, just wide of mid-on, streaky shot
short of a length, slammed with force but straight to deep point
flat on off stump, Hussey steers it to point
tossed up on off stump, Haddin gets forward and defends, Vettori bowls round the wicket
tossed up on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
pushed in just a little flatter, good drift, defended back to Vettori
tossed up outside off, Haddin tries to dab it past third man, hits it to sjort third man and the single is refused
tossed up outside off, cut towards point
punched off the backfoot to short cover, Taylor dives does well to stop that
impeccable timing! full outside off, Haddin stands, delivers, and lofts over long-off for a six
defended towards cover
oof! Styris bowls that on middle and leg, Haddin swings, misses and the ball just misses the stumps
fullish on off stump, Haddin plays across the line and turns it towards deep midwicket
drops the length a little short, haddin gives room and cuts it wide of point
tossed up outside off, Hussey drives it towards sweeper cover
maximum! tossed up on off stump, haddin gets half a step down, lofts effortlessly over deep midwicket
turned towards square leg for an easy single
tossed up on off and middle, Hussey gets forward and steers it to the gap wide point
flighted outside off, Haddin gets on the backfoot and gets o\an inside edge onto his pads,
good length on off stump, cut towards point
short of a lengthj, Hussey gets back and flat-bats it past the bowler, the  ball goes steaming past the outfield
Haddin gets on the frontfoot and drives uppishly towards long-on
short of a length, Hussey punches o\it towards Taylor at cover who does well again to cut that off
slightly short of a length punched towards covers
flatter and faster, Hussey defends towrds the of side
tossed up outside off, Hussey gives room to cut but misses
tossed up outside off, Hussey gets forward and steers it wide of point
Vettori strikes! tossed up on off and middle, Haddin gets forward, plays on the up and spoons it back to Vettori who takes it low, easy take in the end
defended on the front foot, bit of pad, appeal by McCullum
flighted ball drifting on the pads, Hodge turns it towards square leg
punched towards point, McCullum runs across, has a shy at the tumps at the non strikers end, hts the stumps but the batsman was home
drifting on the pads, Hodge scoops it easily towards deep midwicket
width outside off stump, Hodge dabs it to third man
short of a length on middle, cut to point
similar length, Hussey cuts at it hard and a good effort at poit cuts off a certain single
Hussey sweeps, ball hits th pads outside the line off stump, Vettori appeals
struck on the pads, outside the line
tossed up outside off, Hussey dabs it to point, scampers for a single, both dive at their respective ends
pushed towards the off side
short of a length on middle, turned way towards fine leg
short and despatched! Hussey  picks the length early, pulls over the deep midwicket boundary
spears this in on a good length on off, defended on the front foot
Hodge gets a delicate edge towards third man, good length on off stump, Hodge opens the face and glides it easily
defended towards mid-on
pushed towards the off side for a single
flatter delivery, defended on the front foot
steps down but withdraws his stroke, good flight by Vettori
width outside off and Hodge cuts it away past point
take that! McMillan lobs it slow outside off, Hussey gets on one knee and lofts it over long-on
flatter from McMillan, Hussey sweeps it towqrds square leg
Hodge joins in! flighted opn off  stump and Hodge gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it cleanly over deep midwicket
drifting on the pads, Hodge tries to sweep, the ball clips the pads and rolls behind the keeper
ful and outside off, driven down to long-off
tip and run, Hussey plays it with soft hands, ball gets an inside edge onto the pads and rolls to the off side
short, wide and despatched! Hodge cuts it away ferociously past point, sweet timing
better line and length, defended back
full and wide and slower, Hodge gets forward and sends the ball screeching past the covers
plays with soft hands, dabs it down towards the off side and steals a single
slower ball, Hussey leans forward and pushes it towards mid-off who is a little deep
not a bad start, good length on off stump, pushed to cover
fuller, pushed on the front foot past the bowler
pushed in a little faster, Hodge hits it to mid-off
yorker length on off, good stuff! and a bit of in swing as well, Hodge flicks it to midwicket
pushed away towards point, a bit of a mixup but the single was turned down
hit straight to point, good over by Vincent
Reverse sweep! flat on middle, Hussey gets in position and finds the gap
pushed forcefully towards cover
flighted on middle and leg, Hussey gets forward and pushes it to midwicket
flighted on off, Hussey gets to the pitch of it and pushes it to long-on on the walk
tossed up on off, Hodge stays at the crease and places it beautifully behind point, finds the gap to perfection
turned away towards the on side
full toss, swinging in, Hodge slog sweeps it to deep midwicket
pushed towards midwicket for a single
full and Hussey has enough time to get on his knees and loft it over long-on
and another! similar delivery, Hussey hits this straighter, goes plenty of rows back
cut away towards point
Hussey on fire! default mode again! Vincent lands it on a fullish length on middle and leg, Hussey gets on one knee and sweeps it over d\deep midwicket this time
cut away towards point
pushed in flatter towards leg, Hussey gets forward and turns to midwuicket
tries to bludh\geon this one over midwicket, doesnt time it right
reverse sweep again, but doesnt get the placement right
arm ball, Hodge throwns his bat at it, keeps it down and drives it to deep cover
Hodge gives room, drives to cover
full on middle and leg, Hodge swings across the line and midwicker does the fielding

brilliant stuff! slower ball, Hussey gives room to play another slog sweep, plays too early, gets the top edge, the ball is in the air for a long time, Taylor runs in from long on, slides and takes it superbly just inches off the ground
full and on the pads, Hodge turns to deep midwicket
watchfully defended on the front foot
full and on the pads, turned away to the on side
flatter trajectory, Hodge gets forward, then rocks back, cuts towards point
quick single, McMillan has a shy at tye stumps but hits White
short of a length, steps down and flat bats it to long-off
good length on middle and leg, White swings amd connects, the ball races to the midwicket boundary
full toss on leg stump, White hits it off the sweet spot and the ball goes over the square leg ropes
driven to cover
worked away towards deep midwicket
slower ball on leg, Hodge swings it towards deep midwicket
on the blockhole, White just digs it out and shoots off for a quick single, Tuffey runs towards the strikers end and attempts a run out
reverse swing, dug out and played towards fine leg
fullish on the pads, played towards long on
reverse swing again, Hodge backs away a little, swings scross the line, plays it to the on side
and another easy six! Tuffey drops this on on a length, Hodge gets to the pitch and slogs it over deep midwicket, just the right length to play that stroke
fullish on middle and leg, White backs away and swings towat\rds midwicket
swinging in, on the blockhole, White swings but cant despatch it, played to midwicket

appeal! tried to scoop it over the keeper, the ball sneaks thorugh his legs, McCullum takes a catckh diving to his left, appeals, sees that the non striker was half way down the pitch then throws it to the non strikers end, misses
lofted high behind the bowler, lands in the middle of nowhere
yorker length outside off, backs away, misses it completely
driven wide of long-on
low full toss, Hodge backs away and smashes it staright past Bond
beamer! that one slipped out and Bond apologises
another low full toss, Hodge gives room, the ball hits the tip of the bat and races to the deep cover boundary
full on leg stump, slogged over deep midwicket, the fielder sticks his hand out to pull off a blinder but the ball eventually beats him
punched down to long-on
going, gone! rank half volley on middle, White waits for it, connects and lofts it over the straight boundary
yorker on middle nd leg, White plays it to deep midwicket
on the blockhole outside off, dug out to cover
on the blockhole outside off, dug out to long off
yorker length on middle and leg, slogged along the ground to long-on
on the blockhole and dug out to deep midwicket
slower ball, swinging towards the base of leg stump, gets an inside edge onto his boot and the ball rolls to the off side
drifting down the pads, fine leg in the circle and White turns it to the boundary, no chance of cutting that off
swinging in on middle and leg, turned to long leg
yorker length outside off, Hodge throws the kitchen sink at it, fails to beat the infield, takes a single
straying in line again and Tuffey gets the punishment! drifting on the pads, White flicks his wrists and turns it to the fine leg boundary, this time finer than the first one in this over

inn2.comm: good length on middle and off, Vuincent plays it off his pads to square leg
pacy delivery outside off, left alone safely
overpitched outside off, Fleming leans onto it and the ball races past cover, good work by Jaques at the boundary
this one reaches the ropes! overpitched on the pads, Fleming gets forward and works it wide of mid-on
good length outsiode off, left alone to Haddin
good length outside off and shaping away just a tad, left alone safely again
good delivery to start off, on a length outside off, left alone
good length outside off, no away movement, Vincent lets it go
pitched on the corridor just outside off stump, Vincent gets behind the line and defends
pitches on a length just a little wide of off stump, no room to cut, left alone
good length delivery, dips in after pitching, Vincent shuffles a little across his stumps and works it across towards fine leg
short of length on leg stump, gets on Fleming's thighs, he turns it towards the on side and takes a quick single
First blood to Bracken! fullish outside off, no away movement, Fleming plays a lazy shot, sticks his bat out and gets a thin edge to Haddin
drifting down leg, ball clips the thigh pad on the way to Haddin
inside edge, bit of late swing for Bracken
Bracken hurls this one faster, pitches on a length outside off and swings away, left alone
fuller, Vincent gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
outside off stump and Vincent decides to do nothing with it, wise decision
beaten! McGrath holds the length back, Taylor tries to cut but doesnt move his feet
left alone, nearly gets the edge while sticking his bat out
short of a length, Taylor tries to turn to the leg side but gets an outside edge to third man
short of a length outside off, opuched away off the backfoot, well timed, mid off does the fielding
pitched closer to the batsman, sticks his front foot out, hit on the pads
good length outside off, Vincent opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man
pushed to mid-off, batsmen steal a run after the ball ricochets off the stumps
streaky, inside edge just misses the stumps and races to fine leg
swinging s\away, left alone
take that! short of a length, Vincent uses his bottom hand and pulls it over square leg
tip and run, plays it with soft hands and drops it to the off side, good running
Bracken pushes this with more pace, draws Vincent on the front foot, defended
back of a length, comes in after pitching, left alone
good length, comes in, Vincent gets nicely behind it and dabs it towards cover and picks up a quick single
Taylor gets the full face of the bat down and defends
short, in the length to pull, Taylor swings but plays too early
dabbed to point, Taylor sets off and scampers home
good length, Vincent moves across his stumps and inside edges it towards fine leg
good length on middle, Taylor pushes it on the front foot to mid off, takes a single
comes forward to a good length delivery, defended to cover
short of a length, shaping away, tries to heave it on the on-side, hit on the thigh pad
dropped towards mid-off with soft hands and another quick single
pushed past the covers! Bracken errs, overpitches, and Taylor times it well enough
good length on off stump. comes in just a tad, Taylor opens the face but doesnt find the gap, steered to point
pacy delivery to start off with, 150 kmp/h, short and wide outside off, cut away to backward point
short, wide outside leg stump, Tait loses control over that
short of a length on middle, turned away wide of midwicket
short of a length on middle, this one climbed on Taylor, turned away to long leg
fuller and a thickish outside edge flies to the arc between cover and point, Vincent was aiming to hit on the on-side
thats the length! straightens after pitching, Vincent was caught on the backfoot, beaten for pace, Hadding takes it at a good height
slightly wide, goes for the cut, beaten
full and driven straight to mid-off
teasing stuff! width offered outside off, Bracken holds the length back, Taylor swings and misses
on the pads, ball clips the base of the left pad and rolls to the on-side
good length on leg, defended back to the bowler
Bracken gets another! fuller on off stump, Vincent tries to clear mid-off, doesn't get the elevation, Jaques judges it well and takes it behind his body at the edge of the circle
defended on the backfoot back to Bracken
ppeal for leg before! close but sliding down leg just a fraction, Taylor plays all over a full delivery on the pads
full toss on leg stump, Taylor is quick on his feet and he puts it away past square leg
defended towards point
pitched up outside off, Taylor drives at it, gets a thick outsde edge to where second slip would have been
fraction short of a length, punched to the off side
short of a length, drifting towards the body, played off the hips to the on side
full and on the pads, Taylor works it towards fine leg, ball races along the outfield
thick outside edge, taylor does well to play it with soft hands, ball races past the vacant slips
fraction short, hit on the pads
beaten and nearly kisses the edge, Bracken bowls it short of a length, gets it to angle across, Styris sticks his bat out, lucky not to get an edge
fuller and turned towards long leg slightly uppishly, safe shot in the end
pushed towards the off side
ordinary delivery and ordinary shot, wide and slanting away, Styris sticks his bat out without miving his feet
turned wide of mid-on for a quick single
good length, driven to mid off
fraction fuller moving away off the seam, Taylor swings and misses, good stuff from Tait
slanting towards the pads and turned away comfortably towards long leg
short, wide and quick, Tait loses his direction, Taylor tries an upper cut but it was too fast for him
gift on the pads, Taylor flicks it fine, just wide of Haddin
stump tio stump, defended back
reads the length early, works it away to deep square leg, sets off fast, there were three runs for the taking but they settle forn just two
pushed back to the bowler
whack! that was a sight! McGrath gets a little too predictable with his length, Styris steps down, swings across the, connects and the ball screams past the gap between midwicket and mid on
pushed back to the bowler, McGrath does well to get a finger to it
fullish and steered towards point, not where he intended to hit it
chinese cut and he'll take it! pitched outside off, gets the inside edge, misses the off stump and races to fine leg
overpitched outside off, Taylor leans forward, thumps it onto the ground and ball has enough pace to beat the infield, heads to the cover boundary
outside edge, doesn't wuite carry to Hayden at first slip
swung across the line, ball rolls to mid-on
good length, defended back to the bowler
pitched closer to the batsman, Taylor clses the face of the bat and steers it towards midwicket
good length delivery on middle to finish up, defended to midwicket
good length on off, pushed back to the bowler
beaten! Watson pushes this a fraction fuller, draws Stryris forward, doesnt get his bat or body behind the line of the ball
half volley on off stump, curves away, Taylor drives it past the infield and the ball races to cover
drifting on the pads, Taylor shuffles and flicks it to the vacant fine-leg region, with fine leg in the circle that's not the correct line I'm afraid
good length on middle and leg, no away movement, worked to midwicket
short of a length, Styris steps down and makes full use of McGrath's gentle pace, sends the ball hurltling towards deep midwicket
good length on middle, Taylor plays it softly towards square leg, thinks of a single and sends Styris back
fuller and Taylor turns his wrists, works it towards deep square leg
swings and misses! dropped on a good length outside off, plays at it too early
pitched on middle and leg, turned to the onside for an easy two
frction fuller, not much pace, defended with soft hands to mid-off
legcutter, Taylor gets forward and pushes it back to Watson
turned way towards midwicket, takes a single
chipped over midwicket and just beats the fielder
defended to the off side
short of a length outside off, opens the face and steers it point
lazy running! Taylor turns it towards midwicket, Styris charges down, turns back, lucky the throw was wide
short of a length, dips in, worked towards deep square leg
full and slow, Styris steps down a few paces, srives it down the ground, not much power on that to carry it to the boundary
short of a length, Styris swivels, swings and misses, Haddin takes it
punched off the full face of the bat towards cover

sudden rush of blood, good length on middle, Styris plays a little too early, swings across the line, gets the top edge which swirls high to Hussey who takes it a few yards outrside the circle at square leg
turned towards short fine leg, quick single, shy at the stumps at the bowlers end
short outside off, climbs on Fulton, manages to keep it down with si\oft hands
loosener on leg stump, turned to square leg
tossed up on the pads, spins past Fulton and goes to fine -leg
flighted on off stump, driven back to Hogg
pushed a little flatter on off stump, Fulton turns it to midwicket
low full toss on leg stump, turned to the deep
flatter, on middle and leg, defended on the front foot
chinaman, flat on middle, shapes away after pitching, beaten
mid-on for Fulton and he pushes it straight to that direction
overpitched on leg, Fulton sticks his bat at it and turns it to the sweeper at the deep
py\ushed back to the bowler
back of a length, towards the pads, turned to square
short opf a length, attempted to pull, hits the thigh pad and rolls to the off side
defended back to the bowler
hit on the full on the pads, drifts down leg, confident appeal
gets down to swep, gets the top edge,
tossed up on off, tries to drive down the ground, ends up hitting it on the ground, Hogg fields it
full toss and swung to deep square leg
pushed to mid-off on the walk, Taylor scampers home and just manages to beat the direct hit, Billy Bowden upstairs adjudicates
pushed towards midwicket for an easy single
fullish on middle and leg, Fulton gets forward and drives through the line to long-on
good length on off stump, pushed towards the covers
tossed up arounf off stump, Taylor swings through the line, misses, ball just misses the off stump, rolls to fine leg
swept to fine leg
flicked away to deep miswicket
flatter, turning f\in from off stump, turned to midwicket
tossed up on leg, swept fine but the fielder picks it up
Hogg pushes it flat, steered towards point
wrong un to start off, cut away to point
pushed to long-off
tossed up on off stump, pushed to long-off
tucked away towards long-on, excellent running
good length on iff stump, Fulton drops it with soft hands and sets off for a cheeky single
good length on off, comes in after pitching, Taylor tucks it towards square leg
good length outside off, opens the face of the bat and steers it to the off side
punched down the ground wide of long off! this is a superb hundred from one of NZ's finds of the summer
good length on middle and leg, tucked away
fullish, outside off stump, defended back to the bowler
half volley on leg stump, Taylor flicks it square and fetches an easy boundary
full and wide outside off, driven to the sweeper
driftingn on the pads, chipped with ease over the infield, easy two
Tait digs this one in and it climbs on Fulton, left alone
good length outside off, Fulton opens the face and glides it to the right of point
